Largest Countries in the World (by area)

The largest country in the world is Russia with a total area of 17,098,242 Km² (6,601,665 mi²) and a land area of 16,376,870 Km² (6,323,142 mi²), equivalent%%00009to 11% of the total world's landmass of 148,940,000 Km² (57,510,000 square miles).

See also:

Total Area = land area + water bodies (lakes, reservoirs, and rivers)
